//thread class represents a thread of execution

code to be execute in a seprate thread must be implemented as run() of runnable

There are 2 ways of create threads in java

when muliple thread working on different stake then we call thread

-> class MyThread extends Thread {

       @Override
       public void run() {
           System.out.println("Thread is running");
       }
   }

   public class Main {
       public static void main(String[] args) {
           MyThread t1 = new MyThread();
           t1.start();   // New thread start hoga
       }
   }
   Thread class ko inherit karna padta hai.
   Jo code thread mein execute karna hai, wo run() method ke andar likhte hain.
   start() call karne par JVM internally run() ko naye thread mein execute karti hai.


   //////////////

   class MyRunnable implements Runnable {

       @Override
       public void run() {
           System.out.println("Thread is running");
       }
   }

   public class Main {
       public static void main(String[] args) {
           MyRunnable obj = new MyRunnable();

           Thread t1 = new Thread(obj);

           t1.start();
       }
   }

   Runnable interface mein sirf ek method hota hai: run().
   Pehle Runnable object banao.
   Phir us object ko Thread constructor mein pass karo.
   Uske baad start() call karo.


